This is a brilliant idea. Bringing the iTunes search engine into the standalone Soundboard makes it incredibly powerful. You can now search for any song, sound effect, or audio clip in the global database, preview it right in the menu, and instantly lock it into your sound grid!

To make this perfect, I built a hybrid playback engine. The soundboard now seamlessly supports **both** audio types:
1. **iTunes Search API:** Search any track, preview it with the `<i class="fas fa-play"></i>` button, and add it. It plays natively using HTML5 Audio.
2. **YouTube Links:** You can still paste manual YouTube links at the bottom, which play using the hidden YouTube iframe.
3. **Auto-Stop Polish:** I added an event listener to the iTunes audio so that when the sound finishes playing, the glowing "Active" animation on the button turns off automatically!

### Instructions:
Delete everything in your `Soundboard.html` file, copy this completely upgraded code, and paste it in. Save it, and try searching for something like "Vine Boom" or your favorite song!

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no">
    <title>Ultimate Meme Soundboard</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
